   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 06 — Deployment: Docker, CDK & AWS\n",
    "\n",
    "**Session: Month 6, Session 2 (Hands-On Lab)**\n",
    "\n",
    "## Learning Objectives\n",
    "1. Build and run the agent as a Docker container\n",
    "2. Understand the CDK infrastructure stacks\n",
    "3. Deploy the agent to AWS ECS Fargate\n",
    "4. Verify the deployment with smoke tests\n",
    "5. Walk through the CI/CD pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "## Architecture Recap\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Developer push → GitHub Actions → Tests → Docker build → ECR\n",
    "                                                              ↓\n",
    "CDK deploy → SecurityStack → DataStack → AgentStack → ECS Fargate\n",
    "                 Cognito         RDS          ALB\n",
    "                 WAF             Redis        CloudWatch\n",
    "                 Secrets         OpenSearch   X-Ray\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1: Build the Docker Image\n",
    "\n",
    "Run these commands from the project root:\n",
    "\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "# Build the image\n",
    "docker build -t enterprise-agent:latest .\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run locally\n",
    "docker run -p 8000:8000 \\\n",
    "  -e ENVIRONMENT=development \\\n",
    "  -e OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:11434 \\\n",
    "  enterprise-agent:latest\n",
    "\n",
    "# Or run the full stack with docker compose\n",
    "docker compose up\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import subprocess, json\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check if Docker is available\n",
    "result = subprocess.run(['docker', '--version'], capture_output=True, text=True)\n",
    "if result.returncode == 0:\n",
    "    print(f'Docker: {result.stdout.strip()}')\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print('Docker not found. Install from https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check if docker compose is available  \n",
    "result = subprocess.run(['docker', 'compose', 'version'], capture_output=True, text=True)\n",
    "if result.returncode == 0:\n",
    "    print(f'Docker Compose: {result.stdout.strip()}')\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print('Docker Compose not available')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2: CDK Stack Overview"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "stacks = [\n",
    "    {\n",
    "        'name': 'AgentSecurityStack',\n",
    "        'resources': [\n",
    "            'Cognito User Pool (authentication)',\n",
    "            'WAF Web ACL (rate limiting, rule groups)',\n",
    "            'Secrets Manager (JWT secret, API keys)',\n",
    "        ],\n",
    "        'deploy_order': 1,\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "        'name': 'AgentDataStack',\n",
    "        'resources': [\n",
    "            'VPC (2 AZs, public/private/isolated subnets)',\n",
    "            'RDS Aurora PostgreSQL Serverless v2',\n",
    "            'ElastiCache Redis (session state, HITL cache)',\n",
    "            'OpenSearch (RAG vector store)',\n",
    "            'S3 (document storage)',\n",
    "        ],\n",
    "        'deploy_order': 2,\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "        'name': 'AgentAppStack',\n",
    "        'resources': [\n",
    "            'ECR (Docker image registry)',\n",
    "            'ECS Cluster + Fargate Service (2 tasks)',\n",
    "            'Application Load Balancer (HTTPS)',\n",
    "            'Auto-scaling (CPU + memory)',\n",
    "            'CloudWatch Log Groups + Dashboards',\n",
    "            'X-Ray distributed tracing',\n",
    "            'SNS Topic (HITL notifications)',\n",
    "        ],\n",
    "        'deploy_order': 3,\n",
    "    },\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "for stack in stacks:\n",
    "    print(f'\\n[{stack[\"deploy_order\"]}] {stack[\"name\"]}')\n",
    "    print('=' * 50)\n",
    "    for r in stack['resources']:\n",
    "        print(f'  • {r}')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\nTotal deploy time estimate: 15-25 minutes')\n",
    "print('Estimated monthly cost (idle): ~$80-120 USD')\n",
    "print('Estimated monthly cost (active, 1k req/day): ~$200-350 USD')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3: Deploy to AWS\n",
    "\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "# Prerequisites:\n",
    "# 1. AWS CLI configured: aws configure\n",
    "# 2. CDK bootstrapped: cdk bootstrap aws://ACCOUNT/REGION\n",
    "\n",
    "cd infrastructure/cdk\n",
    "pip install aws-cdk-lib constructs\n",
    "\n",
    "# Preview what will be created\n",
    "cdk diff --all\n",
    "\n",
    "# Deploy in order\n",
    "cdk deploy AgentSecurityStack\n",
    "cdk deploy AgentDataStack\n",
    "cdk deploy AgentAppStack\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4: Smoke Tests"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import httpx\n",
    "\n",
    "# Change this to your deployed ALB URL\n",
    "BASE_URL = 'http://localhost:8000'  # or your ALB URL\n",
    "\n",
    "async def smoke_test(base_url: str):\n",
    "    async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=10) as client:\n",
    "        tests = [\n",
    "            ('GET', '/health', None),\n",
    "            ('GET', '/', None),\n",
    "            ('GET', '/api/metrics', None),\n",
    "            ('GET', '/api/policies', None),\n",
    "            ('GET', '/api/hitl/pending', None),\n",
    "            ('GET', '/mcp/tools', None),\n",
    "            ('GET', '/mcp/', None),\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        print(f'Running smoke tests against: {base_url}')\n",
    "        print('=' * 60)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        passed = 0\n",
    "        for method, path, body in tests:\n",
    "            try:\n",
    "                if method == 'GET':\n",
    "                    r = await client.get(f'{base_url}{path}')\n",
    "                else:\n",
    "                    r = await client.post(f'{base_url}{path}', json=body)\n",
    "                \n",
    "                status = '✅ PASS' if r.status_code < 400 else f'❌ FAIL ({r.status_code})'\n",
    "                if r.status_code < 400:\n",
    "                    passed += 1\n",
    "                print(f'{status}  {method} {path}')\n",
    "            except Exception as e:\n",
    "                print(f'❌ ERROR  {method} {path}: {e}')\n",
    "        \n",
    "        print(f'\\nResults: {passed}/{len(tests)} passed')\n",
    "\n",
    "await smoke_test(BASE_URL)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Lab Exercise: Complete the Deployment\n",
    "\n",
    "**For each team (groups of 2-3):**\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Build** the Docker image and run it locally with `docker compose up`\n",
    "2. **Run smoke tests** against localhost:8000\n",
    "3. **Deploy** to AWS (the instructor will provide an AWS sandbox account)\n",
    "4. **Add one HITL test**: \n",
    "   - Send a chat request with a $750 refund intent\n",
    "   - Observe the HITL approval request at `/api/hitl/pending`\n",
    "   - Approve it at `POST /api/hitl/approve/{id}`\n",
    "   - Verify the refund was processed\n",
    "5. **Check CloudWatch**: Find your decision log in `/agent/decisions`\n",
    "\n",
    "**Bonus:** Set up CloudWatch alarms for error rate > 5% and HITL backlog > 10."
   ]
  }
